# Lines starting with '#' are comments.
# Each line is a file pattern followed by one or more owners.

# More details are here: https://help.github.com/articles/about-codeowners/

# The '*' pattern is global owners.

# Order is important. The last matching pattern has the most precedence.
# The folders are ordered as follows:

# In each subsection folders are ordered first by depth, then alphabetically.
# This should make it easy to add new rules without breaking existing ones.

# These owners will be the default owners for everything in
# the repository. Unless a later match takes precedence,
# @username and @username will be requested for
# review when someone opens a pull request.
* @capgemini-axis/administrators

# Code Owners for a file
# *.go @username
# *.tf @username

# Code Owners for a directory
# directoryname/ @username

# All group members as Code Owners for a file
# filename @groupname

# All group members as Code Owners for a directory
# directoryname/ @groupname
